LLM-ready patch: Reduce telemetry flood in development

Target file: lib/offline/telemetry.ts

1) Increase batch size and adjust flush interval in development
Find:
  private batchSize = 50;
  private flushInterval = 30000; // 30 seconds
Replace with:
  private batchSize = process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development' ? 500 : 100;
  private flushInterval = process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development' ? 45000 : 30000; // 45s dev, 30s prod

2) Avoid per-event console logs in development except for notable events
Find the updateMetrics method body where it logs:
  if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
    console.log('[Telemetry]', event);
  }
Replace with:
  if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
    const noteworthy = event.category === 'error' || (event.category === 'network' && event.action === 'backoff');
    if (noteworthy) {
      console.log('[Telemetry]', event);
    }
  }

Notes:
- This reduces server console spam by fewer client flushes and less verbose client-side logging.
